Detailed Interaction Flow – Grocery Image Upload Process

The user opens the CookSnap system and selects an option to upload a grocery image.

The CookSnap system receives the request and validates the image format and size.

The grocery image is successfully uploaded and stored in the system.

The system confirms successful image upload.

A confirmation message is displayed to the user.

This interaction ensures that grocery images are uploaded in a secure and structured manner for further processing.

Detailed Interaction Flow – Ingredient Detection Process

The system analyzes the uploaded grocery image.

The Image Recognition module processes the image.

Detected food items are identified as ingredients.

The identified ingredients are stored and prepared for recipe matching.

This sequence ensures accurate detection of ingredients, forming the foundation for recipe recommendation.

Detailed Interaction Flow – Recipe Recommendation Process

The user requests recipe recommendations.

The CookSnap system analyzes the detected ingredients.

The Recipe Recommendation module matches ingredients with available recipes.

Suitable recipes are generated based on ingredient availability.

The system displays the list of recommended recipes to the user.

This process helps users quickly decide what to cook using available groceries, saving time and reducing food wastage.

Detailed Interaction Flow – Administrative System Monitoring Process

The admin logs into the system using administrative credentials.

The admin accesses the dashboard.

The system collects usage data and system statistics.

The Report module generates usage and performance reports.

The admin reviews reports to monitor system usage and performance.

This interaction supports system monitoring and data-driven decision making for effective administration of CookSnap.
